The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery in an online setting, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm is applied to natural images, which suggests that the paper may also belong to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of conjugate gradient and reweighted least squares also suggests that the paper may belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses an application to short wave infrared imaging, which suggests that it may also belong to signal processing (cs.SI).
